ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Have you ever felt disrespected by a healthcare provider because of your gender identity or expression?
Has a healthcare provider ever: Discouraged you from exploring your gender?
Has a healthcare provider ever: Inconsistently used or misused your name and preferred pronouns?
Has a healthcare provider ever: Refused to care for you because of your gender?
Has a healthcare provider ever: Refused to discuss or address gender related health concerns?
Has a healthcare provider ever: Told you they did not know enough about gender related care to provide it?
Has a healthcare provider ever: Used hurtful or insulting language when discussing your gender?
Has a healthcare provider ever: Asked you what name an pronouns you would like to use?
Has a healthcare provider ever: Discussed that it is normal for people to explore their gender?
Has a healthcare provider ever: Asked if you wanted to talk about your gender?
Has a healthcare provider ever: Supported you in talking with your parent/guardian about your gender?
Has a healthcare provider ever: Asked you what terms you would like to use to describe parts of your body?
Has a healthcare provider ever: Connected you with a local organization or support group?
Has a healthcare provider ever: Connected you with an affirming mental health provider?
Has a healthcare provider ever: Connected you with another doctor or clinic where hormone blockers or puberty blockers are prescribed?
Have you ever avoided seeing a healthcare provider (even though you felt you needed to) because you were worried about how they might react to your gender identity?
Is there a doctor or clinic where you have been seen in the last year for a physical or regular check-up?
Notes: 0=No; 1=Yes, I have been seen in a clinic other than this one for a check-up; 2=Yes, I have been seen in this clinic for a check-up; 3=Unsure; 4=Would rather not answer
